## Output Format

The Content Plan above already provides the overall analysis, themes, and target audience. Reuse and reinforce it — do not reinvent a conflicting interpretation.

Please output valid JSON only, with no explanations or markdown code blocks.

{
  "clips": [
    {
      "id": "clip_001",
      "source_text": "Original segment text, about 100-200 words",
      "start_marker": "Segment start position (e.g., 'first paragraph' or 'beginning of paragraph 3')",
      "end_marker": "Segment end position",
      "summary": "What this segment is about, in one sentence",
      "hook": "The eye-catching text or opening line for the first 3 seconds",
      "title": "Primary title for this clip",
      "golden_quote": "A single sentence that can be turned into a quote card",
      "virality_score": 85,
      "duration_seconds": 45,
      "music_mood": "calm | uplifting | corporate",
      "visual_notes": "Optional notes on visual emphasis, gestures, or slide content to highlight",
      "shots": [
        {
          "time_range": "0-5s",
          "visual": "Visual description for this shot",
          "subtitle": "Subtitle copy for this 5-second segment",
          "mood": "steady | passionate | warm | tense | relaxed"
        }
      ],
      "title_options": [
        "Title option 1",
        "Title option 2"
      ]
    }
  ]
}

Requirements:
- Produce exactly {{ clip_count }} clips
- Each clip's id must be in the format clip_001, clip_002, etc.
- virality_score is an integer from 1-100
- duration_seconds is an integer from 15 to 120
- shots: 3-8 per clip, each 5-15 seconds
- music_mood must be one of: calm, uplifting, corporate
- Output JSON only, no other content
- All fields not in the clips array may be omitted; if present, they must align with the Content Plan above
